# Folder Structure

All gameplay code lives under `Code/` organised by system. Do not put new files flat into `Code/` or a generic `Components/` folder.

## Current systems

| Folder | What belongs there |
|--------|-------------------|
| `Code/Ball/` | Ball state, throw, feel, charge bar |
| `Code/Player/` | Player movement, speed boost, cosmetics, tackles, tackled-player client feel |
| `Code/Network/` | Network manager, connection handling |

## Rules

- When adding a new file, place it in the matching system folder.
- If no folder fits, create a new one named after the system (e.g. `Code/Ultimates/`, `Code/UI/`).
- Never put gameplay components back into a flat `Code/Components/` folder.
- `Assembly.cs` and `MyComponent.cs` stay at `Code/` root (engine files, do not move).
